 <entry>
   <title>How I pimped my TextMate</title>
   <link href="http://www.sideburns.eu/2010/02/25/how-I-pimped-my-textmate.html"/>
   <updated>Liquid error: undefined method `xmlschema' for "25/02/2010":String</updated>
   <id>http://www.sideburns.eu/2010/02/25/how-I-pimped-my-textmate</id>
   <content type="html"><p>TextMate is my editor of choice but it&#8217;s not very sexy at first.</p>

<p><img alt='Vanilla TextMate' src='/images/TMvanilla.png' /></p>

<p>Here is how you can make it funkier.</p>

<p><img alt='Pimped TextMate' src='/images/TMpimped.png' /></p>

<p>The <a href='http://ciaranwal.sh/projectplus' title='Project Plus'>ProjectPlus</a> plugin gives you SCM status badges (Git, SVN, Mercurial, Bazaar &amp; Svk), it swaps the project drawer to a panel for a less tigerish look, it can display Finder colour labels. It can also save project-tree state and sort files and folders.</p>

<p>The <a href='http://julianeberius.github.com/Textmate-Minimap/' title='Minimap'>Minimap</a> plugin brings a drawer with a zoomed-out view of your code a la <a href='http://www.sublimetext.com/' title='Sublime Text'>Sublime Text</a>.</p>

<p>Other plugins worth trying are <a href='http://ditchnet.org/xmlmate/'>XMLMate</a> and <a href='http://www.cocoabits.com/TmCodeBrowser/'>TMCodeBrowser</a> for easy XML and code browsing.</p>

<p>For the aesthetics pimping, I use is the <a href='http://www.monokai.nl/blog/2006/07/15/textmate-color-theme/' title='Monokai'>Monokai</a> color scheme, <a href='http://github.com/kneath/github_textmate_preview' title='Github Web Preview'>Github Web Preview</a> and the green moleskine <a href='http://jason-evers.com/code/code-like-i-do'>icon and splash screen</a>.</p>

<p><img alt='TextMate Splash' src='/images/TMblank.png' /></p>

<p>Now you have the coolest editor that even the VI/Emacs cool kids will envy!</p>

<p><img alt='Pimp' src='/images/pimp.jpg' /></p></content>
